1
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:39,167
<i>I wish this were
just a dream, dear.</i>

2
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:41,833
<i>I wish it were me lying there,
not you.</i>

3
00:00:41,967 --> 00:00:44,733
<i> It should've been me who died.</i>

4
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:47,833
<i>It should just be Manuel
and me mourning Jessica.</i>

5
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:49,167
<i> Now he's sneaked in?</i>

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,400
<i>And he's even brought
his illegitimate family?</i>

7
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:55,367
<i>You really have no shame,
Coleen!</i>

8
00:01:02,067 --> 00:01:05,600
<i>Now you know what it feels like
to almost get run over.</i>

9
00:01:05,733 --> 00:01:07,233
<i> I didn't do anything wrong!</i>

10
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,767
<i> What do you mean, you didn't?</i>

11
00:01:10,733 --> 00:01:11,700
<i> It's your fault!</i>

12
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,267
<i> After she killed you,</i>

13
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,967
<i>she still has the nerve
to visit?</i>

14
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:16,667
<i> She'd better stop.</i>

15
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:17,967
<i> Did she feels guilty?</i>

16
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:21,233
<i>Then she can take that
guilt somewhere else!</i>

17
00:01:21,367 --> 00:01:24,033
<i>And what were you even
doing at Jessica's grave?</i>

18
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:26,100
<i> I wanted to say sorry.</i>

19
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:30,100
<i>So maybe I could feel
a little less guilty.</i>

20
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:34,133
<i> Is that dad?</i>

21
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:37,833
<i>You know, dear, I'm really
trying to accept that...</i>

22
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:39,033
<i> that you're gone.</i>

23
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:42,033
<i>You shouldn't have left,
sweetheart.</i>

24
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:42,967
<i> Coleen.</i>

25
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,400
<i> Go to him later, all right?</i>

26
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:48,933
<i>So, friend,
what's your plan now?</i>

27
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:50,833
<i> I'll start working again.</i>

28
00:01:50,967 --> 00:01:52,200
<i> And I'm moving out.</i>

29
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:54,100
<i> Then why a whole house?</i>

30
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:56,267
<i>I'm preparing
for Manuel's return.</i>

31
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:59,100
<i>Why would Manuel
come back to you?</i>

32
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:01,033
<i> Just wait and see, Alice.</i>

33
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:18,600
We've already spoken
to Atty. Yeban.

34
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,667
What did he say?

35
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:28,100
Apparently, a woman reported her
car missing about a week ago.

36
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:31,333
That same car was found
abandoned by the police

37
00:02:31,467 --> 00:02:33,400
in Fairview.

38
00:02:33,533 --> 00:02:36,500
Was she the one who hit Jessica?

39
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:37,900
No, she wasn't.

40
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:41,233
Her driver borrowed the car,

41
00:02:41,367 --> 00:02:45,167
said he was going to pick up
a relative in Laguna.

42
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,133
It happened to be when
the owner was out of town,

43
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,000
so she let him use it.

44
00:02:49,133 --> 00:02:51,067
However, when she returned,

45
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:54,367
five days later, she could
no longer contact the driver.

46
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:56,167
He's on the run.

47
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:57,333
He's not showing up ever again.

48
00:02:59,167 --> 00:03:03,633
Mom, don't be so negative.

49
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,933
What's important is that,
at least now, we have a suspect.

50
00:03:06,067 --> 00:03:07,167
And like Attorney Yeban said,

51
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:09,533
there's still no official
complaint filed against Coleen.

52
00:03:10,467 --> 00:03:12,633
For now, son.

53
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:16,100
Hazel's been busy with Jessica's
wake and burial.

54
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:21,467
But I wouldn't be surprised
if she decides to sue.

55
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,967
Then we'll fight back, Mom.

56
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:26,300
Attorney Yeban and his team
haven't stopped looking

57
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:28,967
for possible witnesses.

58
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:32,433
So when the time comes,
we'll be ready.

59
00:03:32,567 --> 00:03:35,700
Jeffrey's right, Auntie.

60
00:03:35,833 --> 00:03:37,867
No one has filed any charges
against Coleen.

61
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,767
That means Hazel doesn't
have any evidence.

62
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:44,333
And she won't find any, either.

63
00:03:47,433 --> 00:03:49,833
We need to stick together
for Coleen.

64
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:54,167
Let's show her our support.

65
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,867
And as much as possible,

66
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,367
no one brings up
what happened again.

67
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:03,900
Come on, son.

68
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,733
Let's leave them for now.

69
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:07,000
Let's go home.

70
00:04:41,533 --> 00:04:42,700
Jessica...

71
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,033
Sweetie...

72
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,400
Look at my new place.

73
00:05:04,633 --> 00:05:06,900
If you were here,
I know you'd love it.

74
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:13,133
I miss you, sweetheart.

75
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,500
<i> She was never there for me.</i>

76
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:18,700
<i> Unlike you.</i>

77
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,333
<i> You made me feel loved...</i>

78
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:22,167
<i>you made me feel
like I mattered.</i>

79
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:24,400
<i>And now she wants me
to hate you?</i>

80
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:26,600
<i> Mommy, you're so mean!</i>

81
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:29,167
<i> What did you say?</i>

82
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:32,000
<i>- You're way out of line!
- Hazel, stop!</i>

83
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,133
<i>You talk like
you're so perfect!</i>

84
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:35,533
<i>Why? You think
you can handle me?</i>

85
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:38,633
I'm really sorry.

86
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:39,933
<i> Stop it!</i>

87
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:42,167
<i>- Hazel, that's enough!
- Maybe she needs to get hurt!</i>

88
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,033
<i>- to learn her lesson!
- Jessica is getting hurt!</i>

89
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:45,533
<i> Dad's just sad.</i>

90
00:05:45,667 --> 00:05:47,700
<i>He just wants to feel that
someone still loves</i>

91
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:51,133
<i>and cares for him because
he isn't getting that from you!</i>

92
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,000
<i> How dare you!</i>

93
00:05:52,133 --> 00:05:53,200
<i>- How dare you, huh?
- Hazel!</i>

94
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,733
<i>Dad may not earn much,
but he's still tried, Mom.</i>

95
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:57,433
<i> He's always the one beside me.</i>

96
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:58,900
<i> He never laid a hand on me,</i>

97
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:04,267
<i>so don't be surprised that
my loyalty is with him!</i>

98
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,100
Dear...

99
00:06:05,233 --> 00:06:06,667
I miss you, dear.

100
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:10,033
I miss you.

101
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,133
<i> Mommy!</i>

102
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:17,100
<i> Where's your dad?</i>

103
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,567
<i>- Where is he?
- No, Mommy.</i>

104
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,300
<i>Hurt me all you want,
but I won't tell you!</i>

105
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:23,000
<i> Really?</i>

106
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,167
<i> What do you think will happen</i>

107
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:38,833
<i>when your father finds out
the truth?</i>

108
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:43,167
<i>Knowing dad, he'll still
accept me and love me.</i>

109
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,900
<i>How many times will you
betray me, Jessica?</i>

110
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:46,400
<i> You're hurting me!</i>

111
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:47,533
<i>- Mom!
- You're really a traitor!</i>

112
00:06:47,667 --> 00:06:49,600
<i>You're my daughter!
You're so hard headed!</i>

113
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:52,333
<i> Mom!</i>

114
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:53,333
No, sweetheart!

115
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:56,033
No! I'm sorry!

116
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,733
No!

117
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:00,933
No...

118
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:03,633
No!

119
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:07,700
No! I'm sorry...

120
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:16,233
Jessica, dear, I'm sorry.

121
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,267
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

122
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:23,800
I'm sorry...

123
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:25,033
I'm sorry!

124
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:01,000
Dad.

125
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:05,400
Let's go home.

126
00:08:05,533 --> 00:08:06,900
It's getting late.

127
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:09,400
Go ahead. I'll follow in a bit.

128
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:14,000
Promise you'll come soon, okay?

129
00:08:14,133 --> 00:08:18,300
You need to eat
and take your medicine.

130
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:21,067
You haven't had anything
since this morning.

131
00:08:23,433 --> 00:08:24,300
Dad...

132
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:32,033
if Jessica were here,
she'd never let you skip a meal.

133
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:35,033
She'd scold you for sure.

134
00:08:37,067 --> 00:08:39,000
Dear, I still can't accept...

135
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:43,700
that your sister's gone.

136
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:47,833
That Jessica's really gone.

137
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:58,200
I wish it had been me
instead of her.

138
00:08:58,367 --> 00:09:00,733
I wish I were the one
who got hit.

139
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:04,500
Why would you say that?

140
00:09:06,433 --> 00:09:10,367
So it wouldn't be this painful.

141
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:13,633
You barely got to spend time
with me.

142
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,800
But Jessica...

143
00:09:16,933 --> 00:09:18,900
she's been with you
since she was a baby.

144
00:09:20,733 --> 00:09:23,033
Coleen, don't ever
say that again, okay?

145
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:26,033
No matter how short or long
my time is with any of you,

146
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:29,000
I love you all the same.

147
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:30,600
If I were to lose
even one of you,

148
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:32,133
it would hurt just as much.

149
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:34,400
You are all equal in my heart.

150
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:38,267
Dad.

151
00:09:56,467 --> 00:09:57,333
Friend?

152
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:01,700
Friend!

153
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:04,167
That's enough.

154
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:05,867
Give me the bottle.

155
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,067
- Come on, give it to me.
- What are you doing?

156
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,667
- No!
- I said give it to me!

157
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:12,300
- Stop drinking already!
- Let me drink! Give it back!

158
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,567
It hurts so much, Alice.

159
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:24,400
I miss my daughter.

160
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:29,033
Why is it like this?

161
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:33,600
All I can remember
are the times we fought.

162
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,267
Why?

163
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,700
Why is that all that's left?

164
00:10:41,267 --> 00:10:43,567
Because that's what you mostly
did to her.

165
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:44,967
You hurt her.

166
00:10:45,100 --> 00:10:46,933
You fought with her.

167
00:10:47,067 --> 00:10:48,967
Your hands were too heavy
on her, Hazel.

168
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:53,200
What you're feeling right now,
that's your guilt speaking.

169
00:10:53,333 --> 00:10:54,133
And me...

170
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:58,733
I'm your enabler.
I let you do it.

171
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:01,800
I let you take it out
on my goddaughter.

172
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:09,367
I'm so sorry, dear.

173
00:11:11,633 --> 00:11:12,800
I'm so sorry.

174
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:17,633
I'm a terrible person.

175
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:20,633
I'm a horrible mother.

176
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:23,100
I'm a terrible person.

177
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:26,700
I'm a disgrace.
I'm a horrible mother.

178
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,267
I'm so sorry, Jessica.

179
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,933
Please forgive me.

180
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:31,700
She's gone.

181
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,867
Jessica's gone.

182
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Forgive me, sweetie.

183
00:11:37,167 --> 00:11:37,867
Jessica!

184
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,600
I'm sorry, dear.

185
00:11:58,967 --> 00:11:59,600
<i> Jessica!</i>

186
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:04,433
<i> Jessica, sweetie!</i>

187
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:11,767
<i> Dear, why do you look so sad?</i>

188
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:16,633
<i> Aren't you happy to see me?</i>

189
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,667
<i> I love you, Dad.</i>

190
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,267
<i> I know, dear.</i>

191
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,600
<i>I feel it always,
every single day.</i>

192
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:31,133
<i>Thank you for appreciating
my love, Dad.</i>

193
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:34,000
<i> Thank you for loving me back.</i>

194
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:37,267
<i>Thank you for treating me
like your own child.</i>

195
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,600
<i>Jessica, what do you mean
by "like my own child"?</i>

196
00:12:40,733 --> 00:12:42,000
<i> What are you saying?</i>

197
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:45,133
<i> Jessica, you are my child.</i>

198
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:47,100
<i>I love you so much,
and you know that.</i>

199
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,567
<i>Why would I ever treat you
as anything less?</i>

200
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,533
<i> Dad...</i>

201
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,033
<i> please forgive me.</i>

202
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,967
<i> Forgive me and Mom.</i>

203
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:58,867
<i> Please, forgive us.</i>

204
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:01,433
<i> Jessica, I don't understand.</i>

205
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:02,633
<i> What are you saying sorry for?</i>

206
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,033
<i> You've done nothing wrong.</i>

207
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:07,100
<i> Take care of mommy, Dad.</i>

208
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,133
<i> Goodbye.</i>

209
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:16,033
<i> Jessica, wait!</i>

210
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:20,800
<i> Jessica!</i>

211
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:27,333
<i> Jessica!</i>

212
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,333
Jessica!

213
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:32,000
- Dad!
- Jessica!

214
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:33,600
- Dad.
- Jessica!

215
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:35,267
- Jessica!
- Dad, wake up!

216
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,267
- Dad!
- Jessica!

217
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,267
Dad!

218
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,400
Dad, wake up!

219
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:39,400
- Jessica!
- Dad!

220
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,633
Dad!

221
00:13:41,267 --> 00:13:42,467
- Jessica!
- Dad! Dad, wake up!

222
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,600
- What's happening, son?
- He won't wake up, Mom!

223
00:13:44,733 --> 00:13:45,867
- Jessica!
- Dad!

224
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,933
- Daddy!
- Manuel?

225
00:13:47,067 --> 00:13:49,033
He's having a nightmare!
We have to wake him up!

226
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:50,967
No, no, no! Don't!
What were you thinking?

227
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:53,967
Manuel! Manuel! Manuel!

228
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:56,100
- Jessica...
- Manuel.

229
00:13:56,267 --> 00:13:56,833
Manuel.

230
00:13:56,967 --> 00:13:58,567
Manuel, you were dreaming.

231
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,567
- It's okay now. You're awake.
- It's okay.

232
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:02,400
I saw Jessica.

233
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:03,733
I saw her.

234
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:07,000
I really saw her.

235
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:08,700
It felt so real.

236
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:12,167
What happened, Dad? Why?

237
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:15,967
She said something to me...

238
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,333
but I can't remember.

239
00:14:17,467 --> 00:14:18,833
She was saying sorry.

240
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:22,133
She wanted me to forgive her
and her mother.

241
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:23,567
<i> But why both of them?</i>

242
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:27,667
Does Jessica even have
anything to apologize for?

243
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,367
I don't know.
I really don't know why.

244
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:35,100
Ma'am, what if Jessica
had a secret?

245
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:38,567
Something she wanted to confess
before she...

246
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,467
Oh my God.

247
00:14:41,033 --> 00:14:44,900
What if Hazel is planning
something bad?

248
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:50,667
Or she did something bad,
and Jessica knew about it?

249
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,567
And she took that secret
to her grave?

250
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:08,433
Mom, why did you decide
to have breakfast out here?

251
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:14,167
I just wanted us
all to breathe...

252
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:15,567
to get some fresh air.

253
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,867
To stop thinking,
at least for a while.

254
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:22,333
Dad, eat some more, okay?

255
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:24,200
- It's really good.
- Oh, all right.

256
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,500
There's still more here.

257
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,567
And later, Dad, I'll take you
for a walk around the village,

258
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:28,600
so you can get some sun.

259
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:32,300
Why are you taking dad
out to get some sun?

260
00:15:32,433 --> 00:15:33,333
What is he, a baby?

261
00:15:33,467 --> 00:15:34,200
Yeah.

262
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,333
You're treating him like a baby.

263
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:40,433
What's so funny?

264
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:44,567
And you, Mom,
what's with the sad look?

265
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:46,767
I'm not being emotional, okay?

266
00:15:47,367 --> 00:15:49,767
I just didn't think
this day would ever come.

267
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,567
Us eating together again.

268
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,033
Complete.

269
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,000
Whole.

270
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:56,700
Absolutely.
I still can't believe it.

271
00:15:57,033 --> 00:15:57,900
You know...

272
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,667
I've dreamed
of this for so long.

273
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:03,767
And now it's finally happening.

274
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:07,400
It would've been even more
perfect if Jessica were here.

275
00:16:13,567 --> 00:16:17,067
Even if she's not here anymore,
let's never forget that...

276
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:19,733
she's still part of this family.

277
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:22,567
She'll always have
a special place in our hearts.

278
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:29,067
To Jessica,
our family's sixth member.

279
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:33,000
- To Jessica.
- To Jessica.

280
00:16:38,767 --> 00:16:41,200
Andrea, remember I told you
to invite Joel?

281
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:42,733
Where is he?

282
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:46,633
I forgot to tell him.

283
00:16:47,867 --> 00:16:50,133
He probably went
straight to our house.

284
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:51,933
Figures.

285
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:53,567
You're taking Joel for granted.

286
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:56,233
That's bad. Not good.

287
00:16:56,367 --> 00:17:00,533
You shouldn't take
your boyfriend for granted.

288
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:02,467
Whatever!

289
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,233
Quit it. You're no good either.

290
00:17:04,367 --> 00:17:07,533
Good day, Aunt Felma
and Uncle Manuel.

291
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:09,833
Someone's looking for Coleen.

292
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:11,400
Good morning.

293
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:14,567
Who here is
Miss Coleen Ruiz Cruz?

294
00:17:16,067 --> 00:17:17,467
What do you need from her?

295
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,667
We're just inviting her
to the precinct.

296
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:26,333
We just need to take her
statement regarding the accident

297
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:28,367
that led
to Miss Jessica Cruz's death.

298
00:17:29,533 --> 00:17:30,900
Do you have a warrant?

299
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:32,700
No, Ma'am.

300
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:35,533
It's just an invitation for
clarification purposes only.

301
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,567
It's okay, Mom.

302
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:41,900
I want to help.

303
00:17:51,467 --> 00:17:55,800
Coleen is at the station
right now, Mrs. Cruz.

304
00:17:56,167 --> 00:17:58,767
They're taking her
witness statement.

305
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:02,533
Witness?

306
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,600
Why witness?

307
00:18:04,733 --> 00:18:06,567
Coleen killed Jessica!

308
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:09,700
She should be questioned
as a suspect, not a witness!

309
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:14,600
Mrs. Cruz, let me remind you.

310
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:17,267
What you're saying
about Coleen...

311
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,333
is still just an accusation.

312
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:20,733
We don't have any evidence.

313
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:22,767
Then find one!

314
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:26,867
We've talked to everyone.

315
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:30,933
Not one person said Coleen
pushed your daughter.

316
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,933
The driver in the hit-and-run.

317
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:36,000
He's the one responsible
for Jessica's death.

318
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:39,700
Attorney, I saw it
in Coleen's eyes...

319
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:41,100
in the way she moves.

320
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,433
I know.

321
00:18:42,667 --> 00:18:45,100
That "<i> sisig</i> girl" is the one
who killed my daughter.

322
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:46,333
I'm sure of it.

323
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:48,433
<i> Jessica!</i>

324
00:18:48,567 --> 00:18:49,400
Jessica!

325
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:52,000
<i>- What did you do?
- Nothing.</i>

326
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:54,033
<i> I didn't do anything.</i>

327
00:18:54,167 --> 00:18:55,600
<i> You, Coleen.</i>

328
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:57,000
<i> You have no shame!</i>

329
00:18:57,133 --> 00:18:59,867
<i>You're the reason
Jessica's dead!</i>

330
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,267
<i> You pushed her!</i>

331
00:19:02,267 --> 00:19:04,100
<i> I didn't push her.</i>

332
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,367
Mrs. Cruz, I have to remind you.

333
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:11,500
Be careful with what you say.

334
00:19:12,267 --> 00:19:14,033
That could be grounds
for slander.

335
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:17,633
And, you weren't even there
when the accident happened.

336
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:22,667
<i>- Please, Jessica.
- No!</i>

337
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,567
<i> Hey!</i>

338
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,633
I saw Coleen and Jessica
fighting

339
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,933
before Andrea and I had a fight.

340
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:38,933
I saw it with my own eyes.

341
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:42,100
Coleen was charging at Jessica,
hurting her!

342
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:46,733
Isn't that proof enough?

343
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:48,567
Proof that she meant
to hurt her?

344
00:19:59,967 --> 00:20:01,367
You argued with Jessica?

345
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,933
What was it about?

346
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,400
It was about our dad.

347
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,600
There was jealousy
between us.

348
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:13,100
Can you tell us
what happened?

349
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:15,400
What exactly went on
during that argument?

350
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,733
Go ahead, Coleen.

351
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:21,300
Tell him what happened.

352
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:23,533
Can you tell us what happened?

353
00:20:23,867 --> 00:20:25,767
What exactly went on
during that argument?

354
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:30,167
Go ahead, Coleen.

355
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,000
Tell him what happened.

356
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:36,700
<i> I wish I had never met you!</i>

357
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:39,933
<i>I wish I had never
let you meet dad.</i>

358
00:20:40,067 --> 00:20:41,967
<i> So the truth finally came out!</i>

359
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,400
<i> I wish you'd just disappear!</i>

360
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,467
When we were arguing,

361
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:51,267
I remembered all the...

362
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:55,433
happy moments we had together.

363
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,833
That was when I realized,

364
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:00,267
we're still siblings.

365
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:04,133
That we shouldn't be fighting
at all.

366
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:09,067
I apologized to her.

367
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,867
Because I wanted us
to make peace.

368
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,833
I wanted us to talk
through our issues.

369
00:21:16,033 --> 00:21:16,867
But...

370
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:22,200
<i>- Please, Jessica!
- No!</i>

371
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:25,067
<i>- Hey!
- You want me dead.</i>

372
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:31,500
<i>Then, her mom and my sister
showed up.</i>

373
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:36,600
And everyone just
started fighting.

374
00:21:36,733 --> 00:21:39,533
<i>Stop it, all of you!
Stay out of this!</i>

375
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:41,133
<i> Jeffrey!</i>

376
00:21:41,267 --> 00:21:43,067
<i> Jeffrey, stop!</i>

377
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:46,867
<i> Mom, please stop!</i>

378
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,700
<i> Let go of me!</i>

379
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:51,367
<i> You're always fighting!</i>

380
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:53,433
<i> Always making trouble!</i>

381
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:56,033
<i> Jessica!</i>

382
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:57,567
<i> Jessica, wait!</i>

383
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:01,533
And then?

384
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:09,633
I chased her.

385
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:14,333
I just wanted to talk.

386
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:17,300
Coleen chased
Jessica to hurt her.

387
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:19,667
To kill her.

388
00:22:21,333 --> 00:22:24,333
Mrs. Cruz, I think
you're going too far.

389
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:29,867
Do you really believe that at
Coleen's age, she could do that?

390
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:33,433
Age doesn't stop vengeance
or anger, Attorney.

391
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:39,533
Why would she want revenge?

392
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,800
Because of jealousy.

393
00:22:44,067 --> 00:22:45,333
She admitted it to Jessica.

394
00:22:46,767 --> 00:22:49,133
She's jealous that she grew up
without a father,

395
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:52,100
while Jessica...

396
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:56,933
had Manuel by her side
almost her whole life.

397
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:58,900
And when you came out
into the street,

398
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,700
what happened then?

399
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:06,567
She didn't want
to talk to me anymore.

400
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:12,467
I was trying so hard because
I wanted us to make peace.

401
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:18,133
We were pulling
at each other.

402
00:23:19,033 --> 00:23:21,667
She was struggling.

403
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:27,000
I couldn't save my sister.

404
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:30,433
I couldn't save Jessica.

405
00:23:36,267 --> 00:23:39,933
I couldn't save my sister.

406
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:45,367
You did good. You did good.

407
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,633
It's okay.

408
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,433
It's okay.

409
00:24:00,867 --> 00:24:02,800
They've already sent
Coleen home.

410
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:04,400
- What?
- Well, Mrs. Cruz,

411
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:08,400
the person you want to charge
is telling the truth.

412
00:24:08,533 --> 00:24:10,633
Are you really going
to believe that liar?

413
00:24:10,767 --> 00:24:13,000
Or are you just too lazy
to find the evidence, Attorney?

414
00:24:13,133 --> 00:24:14,967
Fine, if you won't do it,
I will.

415
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:17,400
Do you honestly believe
that she pushed Jessica?

416
00:24:17,533 --> 00:24:18,533
Yes!

417
00:24:18,667 --> 00:24:20,667
That's why I'm so frustrated
that there's no witness!

418
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:23,167
I just want justice
for my daughter.

419
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:27,267
To the driver who hit her,
please, come forward.

420
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:31,400
And to the person who...

421
00:24:31,567 --> 00:24:33,033
pushed Jessica,

422
00:24:33,367 --> 00:24:34,533
take responsibility.

423
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:35,367
Friend,

424
00:24:35,767 --> 00:24:36,800
Coleen's trending online.

425
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:40,967
People are claiming
they saw her push Jessica.

426
00:24:41,367 --> 00:24:42,733
What do you want
to talk about?

427
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:44,900
What you did to destroy
Coleen on social media.

428
00:24:45,033 --> 00:24:46,500
You just want to hurt Felma.

429
00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:47,833
You're even using Coleen.

430
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:49,567
She didn't kill Jessica!

431
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:53,367
If you really believe that,
and have no doubt,

432
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:54,600
say it!

433
00:24:54,733 --> 00:24:57,167
Swear it, right here, in front
of our daughter's grave!
